<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203899>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Afrotrombicula nyongae (Taufflieb and Mouchet, 1959), holotype. A, dorsal aspect of idiosoma; B, ventral aspect of idiosoma (anus invisible); C, dorsal idiosomal seta; D, preanal seta. Abbreviations as in Fig. 5. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B), 20 µm (C, D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203899/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203901>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Afrotrombicula nyongae (Taufflieb and Mouchet, 1959), holotype. A, scutum (eyes not shown); B, dorsal aspect of gnathosoma (lateral palpal tibial seta invisible); C, ventral aspect of gnathosoma; D, leg I, trochanter–telofemur; E, leg I, genu–tarsus (pretarsus invisible); F, leg I, pretarsus; G, leg II, trochanter–tarsus; H, leg III, trochanter–telofemur; I, leg III, genu–tarsus.Abbreviations as in Fig. 6. Scale bars: 50 µm (A, D–I), 20 µm (B, C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203901/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

